<task id="035" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Audit existing `sprk_communication` standard form customizations (UQ1 resolution)</title>
    <phase>Wave 2 — EmailComposer Code Page + Entry Surfaces</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>030</dependencies>
    <blocks>038</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, audit, docs</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Documentation/audit task; outputs a research note that gates the Form Component Control swap decision. No code changes.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>G</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Read-only audit work; only blocks 038 (Form Component Control swap). Can parallelize with 031–034 (which are sequential among themselves but independent of this audit).</parallel-reason>
    <fr-refs>FR-19 (Surface 2 prep), UQ1</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Resolve spec UQ1: when the Form Component Control replaces the default `sprk_communication` form (FR-19 Surface 2 in task 038), what happens to existing customizations on the standard form? Audit and document.

    Investigate the dev environment's standard `sprk_communication` form for:
    - Custom JavaScript handlers (form onload, field onchange, save handlers)
    - Business rules
    - Field visibility / required rules (form-level + field-level)
    - Calculated / rollup fields on the entity (independent of form but affect display)
    - Custom command bar / ribbon items beyond the OOB
    - Sub-grids, related-record displays

    For each finding, determine the migration path: (a) port to Code Page (EmailComposer surface), (b) carry to admin-fallback form (kept per NFR-07), or (c) retire as obsolete.

    Produce `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/035-form-customization-audit.md` with the inventory + migration decisions. This gates task 038's Form Component Control swap decision.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke Dataverse customization analyst. Familiar with Dataverse form customization layers, business rules, JavaScript handlers, and the Dataverse solution explorer.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A research note at `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/035-form-customization-audit.md` containing:
    1. Inventory of all customizations on standard `sprk_communication` form in dev
    2. For each customization, the migration path (port / fallback / retire)
    3. Risk assessment for the Form Component Control swap (R1 in plan.md risk register)
    4. Recommendation for task 038: proceed / proceed with mitigations / escalate

    Decision is binding for task 038 (Form Component Control swap).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Spec UQ1: "Standard form customizations migration. When Form Component Control replaces the default `sprk_communication` form (FR-19 Surface 2), what happens to existing custom JavaScript / business rules / field visibility on the standard form?"

      Per NFR-07 (reversibility), the standard form MUST be retained as an admin/debug fallback. That gives a place for customizations that can't migrate to the Code Page. But we need to know the inventory first.

      Plan.md Risk R1: "Form Component Control swap breaks existing customizations" — mitigation is this audit + NFR-07 fallback form.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/035-form-customization-audit.md (NEW)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec UQ1">Resolve by Wave 2; blocks Form Component Control swap (task 038)</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-07">Standard form retained as admin fallback regardless of audit findings</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Audit dev environment ONLY — do not modify Dataverse customizations in this task</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Research note format follows existing `notes/research/` patterns in other projects (R1/R2)</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If no dev-environment access available, document the audit via metadata files (`Customizations.xml` in the solution) + flag for owner to confirm</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No `.claude/` writes in this Wave 2 task</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/plan.md</file>
